HEADWORD: Slimy
<hw>Slim"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Slimier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Slimiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <def>Of or pertaining to slime;
resembling slime; of the nature of slime; viscous; glutinous; also,
covered or daubed with slime; yielding, or abounding in,
slime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Slimy</qex> things did crawl with legs⟦br⟧
Upon the <qex>slimy</qex> sea.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sliness</ent>⟦br⟧
